  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most countries and is typically addressed under specific criminal legislation. It involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Most jurisdictions have specific laws and regulations that criminalize money laundering, with potential penalties including:\n\n1. Criminal prosecution\n2. Substantial fines\n3. Potential imprisonment\n4. Asset seizure\n\nLaws like the Bank Secrecy Act in the United States and similar legislation in other countries provide legal frameworks for preventing and prosecuting money laundering activities.",
